cat > 0-installation-script << 'EOF'
Steps to install SASS:

1. Ensure Node.js is installed on your system
2. Open terminal/command prompt
3. Run the command: npm install -g sass@1.77.4
4. Verify installation by running: sass --version

Alternative installation methods:
- Using package managers like yarn: yarn global add sass
- Using Homebrew (Mac): brew install sass/sass/sass
EOF